42 (A) Any student of a local school system or public school, a private school, or a home
43 study program in this state;
44 (B) Any student of an institution of the University System of Georgia or a unit of the
45 Technical College System of Georgia; or
46 (C) Any examinee for a professional license in this state.
47 (9) 'Work product' means any written, electronic, recorded, pictorial, artistic, or other
48 form of work.
49 (b) Without otherwise limiting the definition of unfair or deceptive acts or practices under
50 this part, it shall be unlawful for any person, for a commercial purpose, to provide or
51 otherwise cause to be provided any work product to a student or examinee in a substantially
52 completed form that could, under the circumstances, reasonably be considered as being,
53 or forming a part of, an assessment task.
54 (c) No disclaimer or contractual language between a person providing work product and
55 a student or examinee shall exempt such person from the provisions of subsection (b) of
56 this Code section.
57 (d) Nothing in this Code section shall be construed to:
58 (1) Prohibit any person from providing tutorial assistance, research material, or general
59 information to a student or examinee; or
60 (2) Prohibit any person from providing an automated system, software, or platform that
61 generates specific responses to a student's or examinee's prompts; provided, however, that
62 such responses shall not constitute a substantially completed assessment task and the
63 primary purpose of such automated system, software, or platform is not the provision of
64 assessment tasks."
65 SECTION 2.
66 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
